<CENTER><IMG SRC="http://website.lineone.net/~mattgbaker/shagsig.jpg"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/uthorasstormhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoras Stormhammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mr. Wiggle Stick</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#333333>(5/20/01 12:49:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoF anyone?</span><hr size=1> First thing...PoF is less camped than PoH, so this plane requires less timing, more often than PoH, there is nobody here...<br>
<br>
Second thing...These raids require a little more organization than PoH raids due to the make up of the zone...<br>
<br>
Third thing...As Pogue said, they have made a few changes to the things that see invis in PoF, but some things can still see you.  Also, when PoF was revamped they kinda changed the safe areas in the zone...this is prolly why you don't see anyone camped here for days at a time anymore...but the old North Camp that we used invis and run to is no longer entirely safe, that is why you don't see anyone camping out here overnight anymore <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     PoF has really kinda turned into a one-day, need-to-go-pimp-something-but-can't-think-of-anything-else-to-do place to raid.  With the changes to the North Camp (there are roamers that actually pass through the camp, unlike before), the most common tactics for breaking PoF is the SWC breakin.  For the older players, this is an old school tactic and the way that fear was more commonly broken before much was known about it...if I remember correctly, that is how fear was first broken on our server (ask Brice, he was a part of the very early PoF raids...that means he's old too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  Anyways, the SWC breakin is relatively simple, but it does require a few things.  It is done with a breakin team of 12 people (2 groups) who move in to secure the zone before the rest of your raiders enter the zone.  Breakin team requires 1 druid in each group, and a good cleric, enchanter, tank...prolly 1 for each of the 2 groups is best.  What is done is these 2 groups will zone in invis and fully buffed and peel straight for the SWC camp in fear as soon as they zone in. From there they will begin to clear as many of the roamers near the portal and the SWC as they can.  If things start to look bad (too many mobs pulled), the druids evac everyone to Ferrott and we start all over again.  Quite simple actually, just need to be coordinated... once the breakin team clears the portal, the rest of the raid can start zoning in.<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.nagafen.com/images/maps/fearsnag2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
here is a map of PoF, the long blue line from the zone in is the old route for running to North Camp which can also be done, but from what I've heard, the SWC breakin is better, just requires a little more organization...CR is also a little easier for SWC breakin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   it's closer to the portal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Marked on the map is the West Wall Camp, SWC breakin sets up shop just south of there fyi. <br>
